[
    {
        "content": "<p>In Hatcher a covering space of a space <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is defined as follows:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/33k9_9PRkEjryMC1-1OpJnEN/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/33k9_9PRkEjryMC1-1OpJnEN/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/33k9_9PRkEjryMC1-1OpJnEN/image.png\"></a></div><p>While in Mathlib, there's the notion of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Covering.html#IsEvenlyCovered\">covering maps</a>, but digging through the definitions it seems they are different notions. Are covering spaces defined in Mathlib?</p>",
        "id": 438684089,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715731896
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are you looking for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsCoveringMap#doc\">docs#IsCoveringMap</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 438684577,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1715732190
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The def you linked says that a map is a covering map around a point <code>x</code> in the base</p>",
        "id": 438684652,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1715732242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh I didn't realise I linked to <code>IsEvenlyConnected</code> insteaed of <code>IsCoveringMap</code>. But it seems different from what Hatcher is defining</p>",
        "id": 438684762,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715732295
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It requires <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p^{-1}(\\{x\\})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">({</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">})</span></span></span></span> to be discrete whereas in Hatcher it wants <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p^{-1}(\\{x\\})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">({</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">})</span></span></span></span> to be disjoint union of open sets?</p>",
        "id": 438684839,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715732347
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry if I'm like missing something obvious by the way, my topology is objectively bad <span aria-label=\"sweat\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f613\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat\">:sweat:</span></p>",
        "id": 438684867,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715732369
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Think of it like this… if X is a topological space and Y is discrete then <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\times Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> is homeomorphic to a disjoint union of copies of X indexed by Y.</p>",
        "id": 438685599,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1715732777
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And Hatcher doesn’t work with the fiber above x, rather above some sufficiently small neighbourhood of x</p>",
        "id": 438685650,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1715732816
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, I will think about it</p>",
        "id": 438686456,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715733297
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh right in Hatcher it's <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>α</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p^{-1}(U_{\\alpha})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> for one of the covering sets <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>α</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U_{\\alpha}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.109em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, instead of just <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{x\\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span> which is what you're saying</p>",
        "id": 438686537,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715733355
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh okay I get it now. So take the covering map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">S</mi><mn>1</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p : \\mathbb{R} \\to \\mathbb{S}^1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">S</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p(t) = (\\cos(t), \\sin(t))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\">cos</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">sin</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span></span></span></span>, then Mathlib's <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mtext>a point</mtext><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p^{-1}(\\text{a point})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">a point</span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> will be a bunch of discrete points, while Hatcher's <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mtext>an open interval on </mtext><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">S</mi><mn>1</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p^{-1}(\\text{an open interval on } \\mathbb{S}^1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">an open interval on </span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">S</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> will be a bunch of disjoint intervals.</p>",
        "id": 438690138,
        "sender_full_name": "Gareth Ma",
        "timestamp": 1715735523
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I’m not sure what you mean? It’s the same map. And being a covering w.r.t. Hatcher is equivalent to being a covering w.r.t. mathlib</p>",
